AT the Proceedings on the King's Commission of the Peace, and Oyer and Terminer, and Jayl Delivery of Newgate, held for the City of London, and County of Middlesex, at Justice-Hall, in the Old Baily; on Friday, Saturday, and Monday, being the 14th, 15th, and 17th of January, 176, in the twelfth Year of his Majesty's Reign: Before the
Right Honourable Sir FRANCIS FORBES, Kt . Lord Mayor of the City of London, the Right Honourable the Lord Chief Baron Gilbert; the Honourable Mr. Justice Reynolds;
John Raby; Esq ; Serjeant at Law ; and others of his Majesty's Justices; with several of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace, for the City of London and County of Middlesex.
